# =============================================================================
# functions/.env  — shared / project-agnostic variables ONLY (e.g. SMTP)
# =============================================================================
# Copy to .env and fill in your values
# Gmail / Google Workspace: leave SMTP_HOST empty, use App Password
# Microsoft 365: SMTP_HOST=smtp.office365.com SMTP_PORT=587
# Other:        SMTP_HOST=mail.yourdomain.com SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=support@fairflowapp.com
SMTP_PASS=your_app_password
# Optional for non-Gmail:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.office365.com
# SMTP_PORT=587

# =============================================================================
# Stripe — per-project price IDs (NEVER in this shared .env)
# =============================================================================
# Firebase Functions auto-loads .env.<projectId> on top of .env. Use that
# mechanism to keep TEST and LIVE price IDs strictly separated:
#
#   functions/.env.fair-flow-staging      → TEST price IDs (Stripe test mode)
#   functions/.env.fairflowapp-db841      → LIVE price IDs (Stripe live mode)
#
# Each per-project file should define exactly:
#   STRIPE_PRICE_BASE=price_…       Fair Flow – Base Plan         ($99/mo, qty 1)
#   STRIPE_PRICE_LOCATION=price_…   Fair Flow – Additional Location ($79/mo, qty)
#   STRIPE_PRICE_STORAGE=price_…    Fair Flow – Extra Storage     ($10/mo, qty per 10GB)
#
# =============================================================================
# Stripe SECRETS — Firebase Secret Manager (NEVER in any .env file)
# =============================================================================
# The following are never written to disk in this repo. They are stored
# per-project in Google Secret Manager and bound to the relevant functions
# via `defineSecret()` in functions/stripe.js:
#
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY      — sk_live_… (production) | sk_test_… (staging)
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET  — whsec_…   (the signing secret of THAT project's
#                                       webhook endpoint, copied from Stripe
#                                       Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks)
#
# To set / update:
#   firebase functions:secrets:set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY     --project fairflowapp-db841
#   firebase functions:secrets:set STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET --project fairflowapp-db841
#   firebase functions:secrets:set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY     --project fair-flow-staging
#   firebase functions:secrets:set STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET --project fair-flow-staging
